{
  "text": "Studies on the aging process have revealed that the activity of OGG1 changes in an organelle-dependent manner in liver [CITATION_1] , that is, increases in mitochondria and decreases in nuclei [CITATION_2] . The activity of UDG appears to decrease during aging, at least in liver [CITATION_3] . However, skeletal muscle is a poorly studied organ with respect to DNA repair.",
